<section xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
    xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="5.1">
    <info>
        <title>Repetition markings</title>
    </info>
    <para>Apart from the repeat barlines <code>; <emphasis role="italic">|</emphasis> :</code>, you
        can use the following repetition markings:</para>
    <informaltable>
        <tgroup cols="2">
            <colspec colnum="1" colname="col1"/>
            <colspec colnum="2" colname="col2"/>
            <tbody>
                <row>
                    <entry>1st repetition</entry>
                    <entry>o</entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>2nd repetition</entry>
                    <entry>oo</entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>end marking</entry>
                    <entry>o^</entry>
                </row>
            </tbody>
        </tgroup>
    </informaltable>
    <para>The end marking is necessary for the MusicXML/MIDI converter to detect the range of the
        repetition sections.</para>
    <informaltable>
        <tgroup cols="2">
            <colspec colnum="1" colname="col1"/>
            <colspec colnum="2" colname="col2"/>
            <tbody>
                <row>
                    <entry>coda</entry>
                    <entry>i</entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>segno</entry>
                    <entry>I</entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>D.C.</entry>
                    <entry>k</entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>D.S.</entry>
                    <entry>K</entry>
                </row>
            </tbody>
        </tgroup>
    </informaltable>
    <para>Writing <emphasis role="italic">coda</emphasis> or <emphasis role="italic"
            >segno</emphasis> right after <emphasis role="italic">D.C.</emphasis> or <emphasis
            role="italic">D.S.</emphasis> will append "al Coda" and "al Fine" accordingly. </para>
    
    <example>
        <title>Example</title>
        <para>
            <informaltable>
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>Input</entry>
                            <entry>Rendered</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry><code>, D F G Do, D F D Go^:oo D S A Ãœ.</code></entry>
                            <entry/>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </informaltable>
        </para>
    </example>
</section>
